00:03:35.400 --> 00:03:38.170
are just going to get closer
and closer and closer.

00:03:38.170 --> 00:03:40.067
But every time you
calculate the slope,

00:03:40.067 --> 00:03:42.150
it's just going to be the
slope of the line, which

00:03:42.150 --> 00:03:42.810
is negative 4.

00:03:42.810 --> 00:03:44.560
Now, you could also
do this algebraically.

00:03:44.560 --> 00:03:46.360
And let's try to do
it algebraically.

00:03:46.360 --> 00:03:50.760
So let's actually
just take the limit

00:03:50.760 --> 00:03:54.410
as x approaches
negative 1 of g of x.

00:03:54.410 --> 00:03:56.640
Well, they already
told us what g of x is.

00:03:56.640 --> 00:04:02.980
It is negative 4x plus
7, minus g of negative 1.

00:04:02.980 --> 00:04:05.890
So that's minus, what
is g of negative 1?

00:04:05.890 --> 00:04:08.310
Negative 1 times
4 is positive 4.

00:04:08.310 --> 00:04:12.430
Positive 4 plus 7 is 11.

00:04:12.430 --> 00:04:22.210
All of that over x plus 1,
all of that over x plus 1.

00:04:22.210 --> 00:04:24.791
And that's really
x minus negative 1,

00:04:24.791 --> 00:04:26.290
is you want to think
of it that way.

00:04:26.290 --> 00:04:29.630
But I'll just write x
plus 1 this way here.

00:04:29.630 --> 00:04:33.870
So this is going to
be equal to the limit

00:04:33.870 --> 00:04:38.230
as x approaches negative 1 of,
in our numerator-- let's see.

00:04:38.230 --> 00:04:40.680
7 minus 11 is negative 4.

00:04:40.680 --> 00:04:42.120
We can factor out a negative 4.

00:04:42.120 --> 00:04:47.490
It's a negative 4 times x plus
1, all of that over x plus 1.

00:04:47.490 --> 00:04:50.130
And then since we're just
trying to find the limit as x

00:04:50.130 --> 00:04:54.350
approaches negative 1, so
we can cancel those out.

00:04:54.350 --> 00:04:59.120
And this is going to be
non-zero for any x value

00:04:59.120 --> 00:05:00.650
other than negative 1.

00:05:00.650 --> 00:05:03.800
And so this is going to
be equal to negative 4.

00:05:03.800 --> 00:05:05.346
So either way, we
get negative 4.

00:05:05.346 --> 00:05:07.220
But if you just realize,
hey, this is a line.

00:05:07.220 --> 00:05:08.719
It's going to have
a constant slope.

00:05:08.719 --> 00:05:12.190
This is just the slope
of between some arbitrary

00:05:12.190 --> 00:05:19.390
point on the line and the
point negative 1, 11, really.

00:05:19.390 --> 00:05:22.000
Negative 1, 11, you say, well
that's just going to the same

00:05:22.000 --> 00:05:22.958
as the slope of a line.

00:05:22.958 --> 00:05:24.840
It's negative 4.

